<heading box="[400,847,395,421]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" reason="1">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oldroyd" authorityYear="1970" box="[642,847,395,421]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[642,847,395,421]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Congomochtherus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="345" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
This key, modified from that of 
<bibRefCitation box="[515,801,438,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" refId="ref10603" refString="LONDT, J. G. H. &amp; TSACAS, L. 1987. The genus Congomochtherus Oldroyd, 1970 (Diptera, Asilidae, Asilinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 23 (1): 29 - 42." type="journal article">Londt and Tsacas (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, includes a few additional characters. Identifications should be checked by comparing male terminalia with the illustrations provided (
<figureCitation box="[400,516,502,529]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Figs 5-11</figureCitation>
), in addition to those supplied by Londt and Tsacas (1987).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="345" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
1 Katatergal macrosetae predominantly black (accompanied by few, fine white setae) (♂ terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[364,429,609,635]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) (Central Africa) ............................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Oldroyd, 1970" authorityName="Oldroyd" authorityYear="1970" box="[846,1104,609,635]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,933,609,635]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">lobatus</emphasis>
Oldroyd, 1970
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" box="[144,1104,644,671]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">- Katatergal macrosetae yellow-white ...................................................................... 2</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">2 Antennal setae primarily black, a few white basoventrally on scape; postmetacoxal area membranous (bridge absent); female cerci with short spine-like setae (East &amp; southern Africa) ...................................................................................................... 3</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">- Antennal setae primarily white, a few black distolaterally; postmetacoxal area bridged by a sclerotised bar; female cerci fine setose only (South Africa) ......................... 6</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" box="[144,1104,862,889]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">3 All femora with short brown-orange region proximally (East Africa) ................... 4</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">- Femora uniform black (tiny patches of orange colour may be seen but never on all femora) (southern Africa) ....................................................................................... 5</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
4 Anatergal setae black; T1 with at least a few black macrosetae laterally; hypandrium with subapical tuft of black setae (♂ terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[740,821,1004,1031]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) ...................................... ...................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Speiser, 1910)" authorityName="Speiser" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Speiser" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[790,1104,1039,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penicillatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[790,927,1039,1065]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">penicillatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[941,1095,1040,1066]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" refId="ref10860" refString="SPEISER, P. 1910. 4. Orthorhapha. Orthorhapha Nematocera. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Schwedischen Zoologischen Expedition Kilimandjaro - Meru 10 (Diptera): 31 - 112 (Asilidae 82 - 107)." type="book chapter">Speiser, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
- Anatergal setae white; T1 with white macrosetae only; hypandrium with apical tuft of white setae (♂ terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[526,593,1107,1133]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) .................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987" authorityName="Londt &amp; Tsacas" authorityYear="1987" box="[750,1104,1107,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oldroydi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[750,851,1107,1133]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">oldroydi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[857,1104,1107,1134]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" refId="ref10603" refString="LONDT, J. G. H. &amp; TSACAS, L. 1987. The genus Congomochtherus Oldroyd, 1970 (Diptera, Asilidae, Asilinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 23 (1): 29 - 42." type="journal article">Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
5 Mystax occupying more than half the distance between antennal bases and lower facial margin; male terminalia mainly black, hypandrium with a pair of black, narrowly separated setose tufts distomedially (♂ terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[778,845,1214,1241]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) (widespread southern Africa &amp; East Africa) ............................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987" authorityName="Londt &amp; Tsacas" authorityYear="1987" box="[749,1104,1246,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elferinki">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[749,850,1246,1272]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">elferinki</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[857,1104,1246,1273]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" refId="ref10603" refString="LONDT, J. G. H. &amp; TSACAS, L. 1987. The genus Congomochtherus Oldroyd, 1970 (Diptera, Asilidae, Asilinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 23 (1): 29 - 42." type="journal article">Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
- Mystax occupying a little less than half the distance from antennal bases to lower facial margin; male terminalia mainly red-brown, hypandrium with a pair of white, widely separated setose tufts distally (♂ terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[782,847,1345,1372]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) (Namibia &amp; Angola). ........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Oldroyd, 1974" authorityName="Oldroyd" authorityYear="1974" box="[795,1104,1380,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acuminatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[795,933,1380,1406]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">acuminatus</emphasis>
Oldroyd, 1974
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
6 At least a few white setae on posterior part of ocellar tubercle; mystax occupying more than half the distance from antennal bases to lower facial margin; male hypandrium with longish, black macrosetae distolaterally (♂ terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[865,930,1488,1514]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) (South Africa: Western, Eastern and Northern Cape) ..................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987" authorityName="Londt &amp; Tsacas" authorityYear="1987" box="[758,1104,1520,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inachus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[758,850,1520,1546]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">inachus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[857,1104,1520,1546]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" refId="ref10603" refString="LONDT, J. G. H. &amp; TSACAS, L. 1987. The genus Congomochtherus Oldroyd, 1970 (Diptera, Asilidae, Asilinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 23 (1): 29 - 42." type="journal article">Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,395,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
- Ocellar setae all black; mystax occupying less than half the distance from antennal bases to lower facial margin; male hypandrium with short, white setae distolaterally (♂ terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[364,442,1619,1645]" captionStart="Figs 5-11" captionStartId="8.[181,220,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[205,1123,208,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1141,202,1034]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 5-11.Congomochtherus ♂ terminalia (lateral):(5) C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974; (6) C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (7) C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (8) C. lobatus Oldroyd, 1970; (9) C. oldroydi Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987; (10) C. penicillatus (Speiser, 1910); (11) C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472906/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) (South Africa: Eastern Cape) ............................................ ................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987" authorityName="Londt &amp; Tsacas" authorityYear="1987" box="[740,1104,1651,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potamius">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[740,850,1651,1677]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">potamius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[857,1104,1651,1678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" refId="ref10603" refString="LONDT, J. G. H. &amp; TSACAS, L. 1987. The genus Congomochtherus Oldroyd, 1970 (Diptera, Asilidae, Asilinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 23 (1): 29 - 42." type="journal article">Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
